docs.abstract: At least 43 people have been killed in the most intense rains to strike Jakarta, the country’s capital, since record keeping began.
docs.snippet: At least 43 people have been killed in the most intense rains to strike Jakarta, the country’s capital, since record keeping began.
docs.lead_paragraph: JAKARTA, Indonesia — Flash floods killed at least 43 people and left hundreds of thousands homeless in Jakarta, the Indonesian capital, the authorities said on Friday, after the city’s most intense period of rainfall since record keeping began more than 20 years ago.

headline.main: Flash Floods in Indonesia Leave Hundreds of Thousands Homeless
headline.print_headline: Floods Kill 30 in Jakarta as Over a Foot of Rain Falls

docs.abstract: The court was asked to consider whether a prime ministerial candidate charged with serious crimes can form a new government. It ruled that the petition was premature.

docs.lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — With Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu under indictment, Israel’s Supreme Court on Thursday refused to weigh in on whether a prime ministerial candidate charged with serious crimes can be asked to form a new government.

headline.main: Israeli Supreme Court Removes an Obstacle for Netanyahu
headline.print_headline: Israel’s Supreme Court  Decides Not to Decide Yet

docs.abstract: A baroness’s watercolors; Jasper Johns’s crosshatches; a survey of abstract photography; and Alice Miceli’s radiographs of Chernobyl.
docs.snippet: A baroness’s watercolors; Jasper Johns’s crosshatches; a survey of abstract photography; and Alice Miceli’s radiographs of Chernobyl.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 1805, the Baroness Hyde de Neuville (1771-1849) chased Napoleon Bonaparte’s army across Europe in order to obtain a pardon for her husband, an aristocrat accused of conspiring to assassinate the arriviste French emperor. Her plea succeeded, the Neuvilles were banished to America, and so starts the story of “Artist in Exile: The Visual Diary of Baroness Hyde de Neuville” at the New-York Historical Society.

headline.main: What to See Right Now in New York Art Galleries
